<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3974710>
    dc:description "FIG. 8. Fishes from the Coto River basin, Pacific coast, Costa Rica. (A) Polydactylus approximans, 92 mm SL*; (B) Trinectes fonsecensis, 72 mm SL*; (C) Citharichthys gilberti, 64 mm SL*; (D) Pimelodella chagresi, 92 mm SL; (E) Rhamdia guatemalensis, 132 mm SL, (F) 132 mm SL; (G) Rhamdia laticauda, 109 mm SL; (H) Hypostomus aspidolepis, 98 mm SL, (I) 170 mm SL; (J) Rineloricaria uracantha, 120 mm SL; (K) Trichomycterus striatus, 75 mm SL*; (L) Synbranchus marmoratus, 120 mm SL*; (M) Pseudophallus elcapitanensis, 127 mm SL*; (N) Pseudophallus starksi, 118 mm SL. *Pictures taken after fixation in 10% formalin and stored in 70% alcohol." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3974710/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3974706>
    dc:description "FIG. 6. Fishes from the Coto River basin, Pacific coast, Costa Rica. (A) Dormitator latifrons, 106 mm SL; (B) Eleotris picta, 136 mm SL, (C) 196 mm SL; (D) Eleotris tecta, 172 mm SL; (E) Gobiomorus maculatus, 108 mm SL, (F) 158 mm SL, (G) 161 mm SL; (H) Hemieleotris latifasciata, 59 mm SL; (I) Leptophilypnus panamensis, 47 mm SL*; (J) Awaous transandeanus, 94 mm SL, (K) 111 mm SL; (L) Ctenogobius sagittula, 118 mm SL*; (M) Sicydium salvini, 56 mm SL*, (N) 93 mm SL*, (O) mm SL 93 mm SL*, detail of the adhesive disc; (P) Dajaus monticola, 201 mm SL; (Q) Mugil setosus, 236 mm SL. *Pictures taken after fixation in 10% formalin and stored in 70% alcohol." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3974706/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3974696>
    dc:description "FIG. 2. Fishes from the Coto River basin, Pacific coast, Costa Rica. (A) Atherinella argentea, 54 mm SL, (B) 64 mm SL*; (C) Brycon behreae, 139 mm SL, (D) 163 mm SL, (E) 227 mm SL; (F) Astyanax orstedii, 75 mm SL; (G) Odontostilbe dialeptura, 36 mm SL; (H) Pseudocheirodon terrabae, 44 mm SL; (I) Roeboides bussingi, 32 mm SL, (J) 91 mm SL, (K) 92 mm SL; (L) Cyphocharax magdalenae, 66 mm SL, (M) 81 mm SL; (N) Hoplias microlepis, 54 mm SL, (O) 80 mm SL*. *Picture taken after fixation in 10% formalin and stored in 70% alcohol." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3974696/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3974698>
    dc:description "FIG. 3. Fishes from the Coto River basin, Pacific coast, Costa Rica. (A) Lebiasina boruca, 42 mm SL, (B) 87 mm SL; (C) Amphilophus lyonsi, 125 mm SL*, (D) 157 mm SL**; (E) Andinoacara coeruleopunctatus, 40 mm SL, (F) 59 mm SL, (G) 75 mm SL, (H) 83 mm SL*; (I) Cribroheros altifrons, 40 mm SL, (J) 119 mm SL, (K) 131 mm SL*; (L) Cribroheros diquis, 20 mm SL. *Pictures taken after fixation in 10% formalin and stored in 70% alcohol. **Specimen in captivity, picture for illustrative purposes." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3974698/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3974704>
    dc:description "FIG. 5. Fishes from the Coto River basin, Pacific coast, Costa Rica. (A) Oxyzygonectes dovii, 98 mm SL, (B) 103 mm SL; (C) Brachyrhaphis roseni, 32 mm SL, (D) 36 mm SL; (E) Brachyrhaphis terrabensis, 39 mm SL, (F) 61 mm SL*; (G) Poecilia gillii, 72 mm SL, (H) 79 mm SL; (I) Poeciliopsis elongata, 84 mm SL; (J) Poeciliopsis paucimaculata, 62 mm SL; (K) Poeciliopsis retropinna, 38 mm SL, (L) 62 mm SL; (M) Poeciliopsis turrubarensis, 64 mm SL*; (N) Priapichthys panamensis, 40 mm SL*; (O) Cynodonichthys glaucus, 43 mm SL*; (P) Cynodonichthys hildebrandi, 63 mm SL*; (Q) Cynodonichthys uroflammeus, 37 mm SL. *Pictures taken after fixation in 10% formalin and stored in 70% alcohol." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3974704/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3974714>
    dc:description "FIG. 9. Frontal scalation patterns in members of Rivulidae from the Coto River basin, Pacific coast, Costa Rica, (A) D-type, (B) D-type. Adapted from Bussing (1998)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3974714/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3974700>
    dc:description "FIG. 4. Fishes from the Coto River basin, Pacific coast, Costa Rica. (A) Cribroheros diquis, 76 mm SL, (B) 101 mm SL; (C) Oreochromis niloticus, 114 mm SL, (D) 204 mm SL; (E) Parachromis managuensis 72 mm SL, (F) 140 mm SL; (G) Talamancaheros sieboldii, 60 mm SL, (H) 79 mm SL, (I) 82 mm SL, (J) 153 mm SL, (K) Breeding pair, with young**. **Underwater picture." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3974700/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3974708>
    dc:description "FIG. 7. Fishes from the Coto River basin, Pacific coast, Costa Rica. (A) Oligoplites altus, 109 mm SL*; (B) Centropomus medius, 93 mm S*L; (C) Centropomus nigrescens, 113 mm SL*, (D) 170 mm SL; (E) Centropomus robalito, 131 mm SL*; (F) Diapterus peruvianus, 59 mm SL*; (G) Eucinostomus currani, 112 mm SL; (H) 15 mm SL*; (I) Eugerres brevimanus, 151 mm SL; (J) Rhonciscus bayanus, 128 mm SL*, (K) 221 mm SL; (L) Lutjanus argentiventris, 142 mm SL; (M) Lutjanus guttatus, 162 mm SL. *Pictures taken after fixation in 10% formalin and stored in 70% alcohol." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3974708/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

